OL,6,FHe moved off but was approached again
OL,7,Fby Zaarour and words were exchanged,
OL,8,Fprosecutor Jacob Hallam KC said on
OL,9,FWednesday.
OL,11,FOutlining the incident in court, Mr
OL,12,FHallam said: "Mr Khan went to his van
OL,13,Fand turned his back on the defendant
OL,14,Fand started to take off his apron.
OL,16,F"The defendant pulled out a large
OL,17,Fknife, about 16cm in length and 3cm
OL,18,Fwide, which he had down his trousers.
