OL,6,FDuring the attack, a number of Mr
OL,7,FKhan's ribs were fractured, he added.
OL,9,FMembers of the public called emergency
OL,10,Fservices, who were unable to save Mr
OL,11,FKhan due to the "nature and number" of
OL,12,Fhis injuries, Mr Hallam said.
OL,14,FZaarour, 26, from Brent, north-west
OL,15,FLondon, was arrested at his home the
OL,16,Ffollowing day and charged with murder
OL,17,Fand possession of a blade.
